    Paul Bourke3 years ago on Google
    4/5
    A nice clean comfortable Hilton branded hotel in the heart on Tangiers. Its location is very convenient as the new high speed train (TGV) Station has just opened (Nov18) and its a short walk of about 5 to 8 minutes from the hotel. So you 
    A nice clean comfortable Hilton branded hotel in the heart on Tangiers. Its location is very convenient as the new high speed train (TGV) Station has just opened (Nov18) and its a short walk of about 5 to 8 minutes from the hotel. So you can now get the bullet train from Tangiers to Casablanca and be there in around 2 hours which is half the old 4 hours commute time by car. It will be good for business travelers who fly in to Casablanca but who need to also come to Tangiers. You obviously have more connecting flight choices out of Casablanca than you do the local Tangiers Airport. Hotel staff friendly, attentive and helpful. But remember where you are and respect the culture. Hotel rooms have ironing board (mine was missing the iron this time) kettle and basic amenities to make coffee or tea. There is a unstocked minibar fridge as well as a lockable safe in each room. There is a shopping mall right next door about a 2 minute walk so you can buy some groceries snacks sodas extra water etc. there to stock the room fridge. There are two complimentary bottles of water on arrival that is not restocked after the first day. Bathroom, shower and toilet clean, tidy and reasonably modern. An ocean view room is worth the extra investment per night if thats important to you. A very generous serving of foods and choices st breakfast. One of the better ones I have had. A on duty chef will cook you a fresh omelette and you can make fresh waffles too. Good choice of fruits, yogurts, breads, and most importantly, coffee. The hotel is right across from the beach and the new pier thats been built and there lots of local restaurants close by. There is also a small food court in the shopping mall next door. There money changers next door if you need to convert some currency and ATMs close by. For fast food junkies and go keep the kids happy, theres a MacDonalds next door!

    About this hotel

    A 6-minute walk from the municipal beach, this refined hotel is 2 minutes' walk from Tanger Ville train station, 2 km from Tanja Marina Bay and 14 km from Tangier Ibn Battouta Airport.

    Airy, modern rooms, some with sea views, feature flat-screen TVs and Wi-Fi, as well as minifridges, and tea and coffeemaking facilities. Upgraded rooms add sofabeds, and suites provide separate living rooms. Room service is available.

    There's an international grill restaurant, a bar and a 24-hour convenience store. Other amenities include a fitness center and a coin-operated laundry, as well as 3 meeting rooms and a 24/7 business center. Parking is available.

    Check-out time: 12:00 PM
